The paper discusses systems for probabilistic reasoning, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on qualitative probabilistic networks suggests a potential connection to the subfield of symbolic AI (cs.SI), which deals with reasoning and knowledge representation. The paper also discusses refining the representation of these networks, which could involve techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
